    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Rear Bumper Assembly</title>
        <para>The rear bumper assembly is a steel bumper bolted to the chassis frame section offset with mounting
            brackets. The bumper is mounted to the brackets with eight carriage bolts with lock nuts and washers.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate, loosen and remove the mounting screws securing the bumper transition cover on the
                body panels and bumper ends.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47004115" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/G47004115.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 115. Bumper Transition Cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. REAR BUMPER SIDE MOUNTING BOLTS (2 EACH SIDE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REAR BUMPER MOUNTING BOLTS (4)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BUS REAR BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BUMPER TRANSITION COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BUMPER TRANSITION COVER MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the bumper mounting bolts and lock nuts and washers on the bumper assembly. These
                bolts are located on the outboard section of the bumper assembly on each side at the rear of the bus
                body.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47004116" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/G47004116.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 116. Rear Bumper Side Support Brackets (DRIVERS SIDE SHOWN)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. REAR BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REAR BUMPER SIDE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. REAR BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT BRACKET ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the lock nuts and washers (2 each side) securing the bumper assembly to
                the mounting brackets on the bumper mounting assembly located outboard each side of the body.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47004117" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47004117.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 117. Bumper Mounting Bracket and Bolts with Tow Hook Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SQUEAK PAD</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BUMPER FRAME MOUNTING BRACKET BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. REAR BUMPER MOUNTING BOLTS, NUTS AND WASHERS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. REAR BUMPER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>5. REAR BUMPER LOWER FLANGE SECTION</callout1>
                <callout1>6. REAR TOW HOOK ASSEMBLY (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                <callout1>7. CHASSIS FRAME SECTION</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant steadying the bumper, loosen and remove the remaining 4 mounting bolts at
                the rear of the bumper assembly from the bumper mounting brackets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bumper assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
